dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.5.0.6491
dataIdInfo.idPurp:
Feature class contains an inventory of all Outdoor Grants Funded Parks, all city park, all county parks, some school parks, and a few private park facilities. This feature class is intended for a many different purposes.
It helps keep track of park name lineage making it easier to trace back which grants were associated with which parks when park names change. It helps derive statistics about funded park facilities. It assists with funded park inspections. It acts as an inventory of all city and county parks in the state. It also serves as a reference for project officers to see how many parks a sponsor, which gives them an opportunity to, go to them.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
parkNum - The unique park number for the park. It was arbitrarily generated. It can be joined and related to other feature classes that have this park number field.

currentNam - The primary park name which is most resent. Might be inaccurate but it is our best guess.

pastName - A "/" character separated list of all secondary or past names for the park.

InspDate - The date at which the park was last inspected.

Type this is the primary symbology field. It attempts the break down the different parks into categories that are the most useful for the project officers

  • educational a park that is associated with a grade school or university. May or may not be available to the public for use.

  • funded park a park that has been funded by at least one of the three grant programs ORGP operated (this includes matching grants, fun parks and trails for life)

  • non funded public park facilities that are run by municipalities and counties. The ORGP program has not spent any funding inside of these parks. They might have applied or withdrew for a grant at the park but no actual program funds have been spent at these locations.

  • private a privately owned or operated recreational site. Includes churches, non-profits, youth camps, veterans groups, property owner association parks, apartment complex parks and other private sites.

Fed6f3Stat

  • Has 6(f)3 boundary - Currently active park site which has LWCF 6(f)3 restrictions on it.

  • entire park converted a park that was entirely converted through the LWCF conversion process and replaced. Only given this status for a full conversion park rather than a Partial conversion.

  • lease expired - NPS Letter Park facilities where the National park service released a property from LWCF 6f3 protection because of an expired lease. In the early year of the LWCF program (1960-1990), projects and 6f3 boundaries were allowed on leased land but it caused many issues so the practice was mostly discontinued. As leases on these old LWCF parks expire so does the 6f3 protection but it requires the approval of the National Park Service.

  • NPS Dismissal these dismissals are strange. They still result in the 6(f)3 boundary becoming effectively non-existent. They do not follow any clear pattern.

  • N/A The federal status of these parks is non-applicable because they did not receive LWCF grant funding.

state6f3Status

  • Has 6(f)3 boundary - Currently active park site which has LWCF 6(f)3 restrictions on it.

  • ANCRC lease Expired a lease expiration resulted in the dismissal of the sites long term 6(f)3 obligations.

  • Pending project closing park currently has an open project on it. When the project closes it will have a 6(f)3 boundary.

  • N/A The federal status of these parks is non-applicable because they did not receive LWCF grant funding.

sponsorshi - Sponsorshi the name of the sponsor which the program defaults to for responsibility for 6(f)3 or project boundary obligations for matching grants. It is defined as the sponsor of the last grant given at the park. If the grant is given to a school district and a local sponsor include both on the list. Please note this does not include all previous sponsors of the grant if there are multiple. The intent is to set the sponsor to the group that feels responsible for the property.

inspaCycle a field value which indicates if the park is part of the park inspection cycle for this year. Depending on circumstances, the group might include areas outside of the inspection region and exclude some parks, which might have been dismissed or visited recently by other staff.

source - The source of the park footprint geometry information

note1 - General notes about the park site and any unique situations or unresolved data quality issues with the park.

calc_acre - The area of the park in acres according to the GIS geometry.

acre_area - The area of the park according to the park managing agency, deed, or other official documents.

mgntOrg - An educated guess at which organization manages the park.

googleLink a hyper link to a google page which drops a pin at the center of the park. Can be useful for getting directions to the park. Field value is hard coded so it must be updated periodically.

mgntOrgType - An arbitrary category for the management organization. Many of the categories overlap. Simply choose which one made the most sense.

  • Apartment complex the managing organization is an apartment complex managing firm.

  • Church the group that operates the park is a church group of some kind. Most likely a Christian church.

  • City group is a municipality of some kind

  • Community group is an unincorporated community. The park is most likely under the jurisdiction of the county but members of the unincorporated community are the ones that actually clean up and repair the park facilities.

  • County groups is a county government

  • day care group is a day care center for small children

  • federal group is a federal government agency

  • inidan nation group is an Indian tribe

  • non profit group is a nonprofit such as a youth or summer camp organization

  • property owners association group is an association of property owners or a home owners association. Members are most likely live in the immediate area.

  • school district group is a school district which operates the school that is adjacent to the park.

  • State the group is a government state agency

  • University group is a higher education institution such as a college or university.

  • Unknown management group is completely known

  • water company management group is a private water company providing some public services.

city - the name of the city that the park is located inside of. If the park is located outside of the incorporated boundaries of a city, the field is given a value of unincorporated area rather than a municipality name.

county - the name of the county or counties the park is located in. if the park is located in multiples counties, all counties are listed in the field.

wetland - indicates if the park touches a wetland of some kind. This was determined using the high resolution national hydrology dataset.

floodplain - indicates if the park is located inside of a mapped special flood hazard area. This was determined using the federal emergency management agencys GIS flood hazard dataset.

gpsCoordin - The GPS coordinates of for the primary entrance to the facility. This data was translated over from the park entrances feature class.

STR - all of the Section, Township and Ranges that the park is park of. Field was populated using the Arkansas Department of Transportation PLSS data set using a custom written python tool.

webAppLink - A hyperlink to the main ORGP GIS web app which auto zooms to the extent of the polygon feature. Generated using a python tool but could be done using field calculator.

Maintenance instructions

Out of all of the ORGP GIS Dataset this is the one with the most hard coded information in it. Due to the need to have this information show up in web apps and in File Maker Pro the data needed to be hard coded. This means fields such as city, county, wetland, floodplain, gpscoordin, STR, webAppLink and calc_acre all need to change which the feature geometry changes. Periodically run field calculations and python tools to keep this information up to date.

The sponsorship field and type field need to be updated as existing non-funded parks become funded. New parks need to be added to the dataset as they get built and old parks, which are demolished need to be removed.

Coordinate system is NAD_1983_UTM_Zone_15N
